<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Numeral_systems">Numeral sy=
stems</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DArithm=
etic&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Numeral syst=
ems"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numeral_system" titl=
e=3D"Numeral system">Numeral system</a></div>
<p>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numerical_digit" title=3D"Num=
erical digit">numeral</a> is a symbol to represent a number and numeral sys=
tems are representational frameworks.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-29" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic#cite_note-29"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> They usually have a limited amount of basic numerals, which direct=
ly refer to certain numbers. The system governs how these basic numerals ma=
y be combined to express any number.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-30" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic#cite_note-30"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> Numeral systems are either <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Positional" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Positional">positional</a> or n=
on-positional. All early numeral systems were non-positional.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-31" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arit=
hmetic#cite_note-31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For non-positional numeral systems, the va=
lue of a digit does not depend on its position in the numeral.<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-32" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ari=
thmetic#cite_note-32"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
