<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egyptian_hieroglyphics" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Egyptian hieroglyphics">Egyptian hieroglyphics</a=
> had a more complex non-positional <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Egyptian_numerals" title=3D"Egyptian numerals">numeral system</a>. They h=
ave additional symbols for numbers like 10, 100, 1000, and 10,000. These sy=
mbols can be combined into a sum to more conveniently express larger number=
s. For instance, the numeral for 10,405 uses one time the symbol for 10,000=
, four times the symbol for 100, and five times the symbol for 1. A similar=
 well-known framework is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman=
_numeral_system" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Roman numeral system">Roman=
 numeral system</a>. It has the symbols I, V, X, L, C, D, M as its basic nu=
merals to represent the numbers 1, 5, 10, 50, 100, 500, and 1000.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-36" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Arithmetic#cite_note-36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>33<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>A numeral system is positional if the position of a basic numeral in=
 a compound expression determines its value. Positional numeral systems hav=
e a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radix" title=3D"Radix">radix</=
a> that acts as a multiplicand of the different positions. For each subsequ=
ent position, the radix is raised to a higher power. In the common decimal =
system, also called the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindu%E2%8=
0%93Arabic_numeral_system" title=3D"Hindu=E2=80=93Arabic numeral system">Hi=
ndu=E2=80=93Arabic numeral system</a>, the radix is 10. This means that the=
 first digit is multiplied by <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-elem=
ent-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" sty=
le=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" al=
ttext=3D"{\displaystyle 10^{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>10</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 10^{0}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/45d6ef004bb97df6bf6ee2ec20f8eec7aa32adcb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
