eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic#cite_note-37"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup>
</p><p>Another positional numeral system used extensively in <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_arithmetic" title=3D"Computer arithmeti=
c">computer arithmetic</a> is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Binary_system" title=3D"Binary system">binary system</a>, which has a radix=
 of 2. This means that the first digit is multiplied by <span class=3D"mwe-=
math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline=
 mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w=
3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle 2^{0}}">
