><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>71<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup> A common technique used for division is called <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_division" title=3D"Long division">long divis=
ion</a>. Other methods include <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sho=
rt_division" title=3D"Short division">short division</a> and <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chunking_(division)" title=3D"Chunking (division=
)">chunking</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-77" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
