er/svg/65b76f90e4b9aca0b04535656af0a55be506accf" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.338ex; width:10.913ex; height:3.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
tfrac {2}{7}}+{\tfrac {3}{7}}=3D{\tfrac {5}{7}}}"></span>. A similar proced=
ure is used for subtraction. If the two numbers do not have the same denomi=
nator then they must be transformed to find a common denominator. This can =
be achieved by scaling the first number with the denominator of the second =
number while scaling the second number with the denominator of the first nu=
mber. For instance, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline=
"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"disp=
lay: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{=
\displaystyle {\tfrac {1}{3}}+{\tfrac {1}{2}}=3D{\tfrac {1\cdot 2}{3\cdot 2=
}}+{\tfrac {1\cdot 3}{2\cdot 3}}=3D{\tfrac {2}{6}}+{\tfrac {3}{6}}=3D{\tfra=
c {5}{6}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mn>3</mn>
